data.name: _sampleTaskDialog.Content
data.value: Task dialogs are a more flexible type of message box. Among other things, task dialogs support custom buttons, command links, scroll bars, expandable sections, radio buttons, a check box (useful for e.g. "don't show this again"), custom icons, and a footer. Some of those things are demonstrated here.

data.name: _sampleTaskDialog.ExpandedInformation
data.value: Ookii.org's Task Dialog doesn't just provide a wrapper for the native Task Dialog API; it is designed to provide a programming interface that is natural to .Net developers, and offers full Windows Forms designer support.

data.name: _sampleInputDialog.Content
data.value: Input dialogs offer an easy way to prompt the user for single piece of text. It's like an improved version of the old Visual Basic InputBox function. Input dialogs use a style similar to task dialogs when running on Windows Vista or later. They also support password masking.
